<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">PARMESAN POPCORN</div>



<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page066.article001.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>

<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY SARAH SWIHART</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 12 to 15 servings </p><br/><p class="no-indent">½ cup grated Parmesan cheese </p><p class="no-indent">2 teaspoons salt </p><p class="no-indent">½ teaspoon garlic powder </p><p class="no-indent">½ teaspoon ground black pepper </p><p class="no-indent">6 tablespoons oil, divided </p><p class="no-indent">1½ cups popcorn kernels, divided </p><p class="no-indent">¼ cup butter, melted </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. In a small bowl, combine Parmesan, salt, garlic powder, and pepper. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. In a large Dutch oven, heat 3 tablespoons oil over medium heat. Add 3 popcorn kernels, and cover until they pop. Add ¾ cup kernels, cover, and shake pan continuously over burner for 2 to 4 minutes or until popcorn is completely popped. Transfer popcorn to a large bowl, discarding any unpopped kernels. Repeat procedure with remaining 3 tablespoons oil and remaining ¾ cup popcorn kernels. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">3. Drizzle popcorn with melted butter, tossing to coat. Sprinkle Parmesan mixture over popcorn, tossing gently to coat. Store in airtight containers for up to 3 days.</p></div>
